                                                         Student Management System
 1. Introduction:

The Student Management System is a console-based application developed using C++. The main purpose of this system is to manage student records efficiently. It helps users to add, display, search, and delete student records easily using file handling operations.

This system reduces manual work and improves student record management by maintaining details such as Student ID, Student Name, and Marks in an organized manner.

2. Objectives:

• To maintain student records efficiently.
• To reduce manual errors in student management.
• To provide quick searching of student details.
• To display all student records easily.
• To remove unnecessary student records.
• To learn file handling concepts using C++.

 3. System Features:

 Main Features

1. Add New Student Record
2. Display All Student Records
3. Search Student by ID
4. Delete Student Record
5. Menu Driven User Interface
6. File Handling for Data Storage
7. Easy Console-Based Operation

4. Technologies and Concepts Used:

Technologies Used
• Programming Language: C++
• Platform: Console Application
• Compiler: Dev C++

Concepts Used

• Structures (struct)
• Functions
• File Handling
• Loops (while, do-while)
• Conditional Statements (if, switch)
• Character Arrays
• Input and Output Streams



 5. System Design:

Structure Design

 Structure: Student

| DATA MEMBERS | DESCRIPTION          |
| ------------ | -------------------- |
| ID           | Stores Student ID    |
| NAME         | Stores Student Name  |
| MARKS        | Stores Student Marks |

Functions

| FUNCTION          | PURPOSE                      |
| ----------------- | ---------------------------- |
| addStudent()      | Adds student details         |
| displayStudents() | Displays all student records |
| searchStudent()   | Searches student by ID       |
| deleteStudent()   | Deletes student record       |

6. Workflow:

Step-by-Step Working Process

1. Program starts.
2. Main menu is displayed.
3. User selects an option.
4. Based on choice:
   • Add student record
   • Display student records
   • Search student
   • Delete student
5. System performs selected operation.
6. Menu repeats until user chooses Exit.
7. Program terminates.

